node.text:
.
I happen to drive by the dump site I use to goto 2-3 day a week, so I figure I share an insight into my past.
.
15 years ago, I bought my first company truck at the age of 24. Although I was the boss, I was also the truck driver and trash hauler. When you are a small company you have to do everything and that includes picking up construction debris, hauling, and driving to the dump. I remember how awful the trash dump smells, but it helps you appreciate the better things in life.
.
I didn’t start off working at a designer’s fancy office or showroom wearing fancy clothes and looking pretty. Just a young kid with a baseball cap chasing a big dream doing whatever I can to earn a buck. Sometimes people see the image of success but don’t realize the sweat and tears behind the scenes.
.

One thing I like about designing the exterior vs interior is the freedoms of shapes and objects. For example a swimming pool like this can be very abstract shape and still be functional due to the size so we have more creative freedom. With the inside it’s harder to create abstract shapes like this because of space restrictions. Interior is more like designing within a parameter and making it pretty and functional. The exterior is more like designing outside the box with more freedom and more unique property shapes. It’s fun to do both so that’s why we dabble in both.

node.text:
O U T D O O R  K I T C H E N
Provides a different dining and entertaining experience than indoor kitchens. When we create an outdoor kitchens, it’s not just making a functional area to cook outside, but it’s an area to cook and entertain in a beautiful environment.
.
For this project, the client is a restauranteur that wanted a unique cooking and dining experience for their guests. So we designed and built this pond that wraps around the outdoor kitchen with a waterwall spanning the back. As the guests dine, they see the chef in action as well as the waterfall through the window right in front of them. To the left they have a magnificent night view of the city and to the right they have a beautiful pond with a zen garden in it.
.
While they dine, they are surrounded by the soothing sounds of the water as it trickles down the stone on the waterwall in the background. In the foreground they hear sizzling sound of the food as it’s being cooked while the food aroma is in the air. As they are done with the main course, they can sit down in the sunken seating area for dessert and tea and enjoy the tranquil water that surrounds it as they wind down. I am not sure even a 3 Michelin star restaurant can match the same dining experience.
.
What do you think? Who would like this kind of outdoor cooking and dinning experience? Like, save, and comment below.

.
I happen to drive by the dump site I use to goto 2-3 day a week, so I figure I share an insight into my past.
.
15 years ago, I bought my first company truck at the age of 24. Although I was the boss, I was also the truck driver and trash hauler. When you are a small company you have to do everything and that includes picking up construction debris, hauling, and driving to the dump. I remember how awful the trash dump smells, but it helps you appreciate the better things in life.
.
I didn’t start off working at a designer’s fancy office or showroom wearing fancy clothes and looking pretty. Just a young kid with a baseball cap chasing a big dream doing whatever I can to earn a buck. Sometimes people see the image of success but don’t realize the sweat and tears behind the scenes.
.
